mentation—the bravura of which spurred on developments in critical theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Books & Reading.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishz978311099395008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2022z9783110994186oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074977940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300268201?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300268201423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300268201/original  a978-3-11-074977-9  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099395-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-SEWb2022